                            <comment id="14647135" author="kizune" created="Tue, 6 Feb 2024 12:09:17 -0800"  >The reason is that Aqua look and feel is unique in how it handles overflow of tabs in JTabbedPane - unlike other LaF&amp;#39;s it completely hides the tab that does not feet the tab width rather than wrapping it to another row. Because of that the location and size of the tab is being returned as null and JTabbedPane accessibility code does not handle it well.</comment>
                            <comment id="14644484" author="kizune" created="Mon, 29 Jan 2024 13:43:00 -0800"  >I can reproduce it on the current sources and in jdk21 so it seems to be related to the way JTabbedPane fetches its location on screen.</comment>
                            <comment id="14644468" author="vdyakov" created="Mon, 29 Jan 2024 12:32:29 -0800"  >[~asemenov] could you please take a look and fix this NPE as caused by &lt;a href=&quot;https://bugs.openjdk.org/browse/JDK-8264303&quot; title=&quot;Create implementation for NSAccessibilityTabGroup protocol peer&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;JDK-8264303&quot;&gt;&lt;strike&gt;JDK-8264303&lt;/strike&gt;&lt;/a&gt; changeset</comment>
                            <comment id="14644444" author="prr" created="Mon, 29 Jan 2024 11:07:15 -0800"  >FYI, I cannot reproduce it with 8GA, 8u291, 8u331, or 8u341 but as soon as reach 8u351 I can reproduce it.&lt;br/&gt;
Also reproduces with 8u381.&lt;br/&gt;
So I think this a regression from the Mac A11Y re-write and which was backported to 8u and I expect it&amp;#39;ll show up in all the updates that got the backports. For mainline it is probably something like JDK 18 that introduced it - that&amp;#39;s a guess - you should confirm it.</comment>
